<content>
    <para id="id1165026918216">After completing this chapter, you should</para>
    
    <list id="id1165024703334" list-type="bulleted"><title>Estimation by Rounding (<link document="m35011"/>)</title><item>understand the reason for estimation</item>
      <item>be able to estimate the result of an addition, multiplication, subtraction, or division using the rounding technique</item>
    </list>
    
    <list id="id1165024674936" list-type="bulleted"><title>Estimation by Clustering (<link document="m35012"/>)</title><item>understand the concept of clustering</item>
      <item>be able to estimate the result of adding more than two numbers when clustering occurs using the clustering technique</item>
    </list>
    
    <list id="id1165026567353" list-type="bulleted"><title>Mental Arithmeticâ€”Using the Distributive Property (<link document="m35013"/>)</title><item>understand the distributive property</item>
      <item>be able to obtain the exact result of a multiplication using the distributive property</item>
    </list>
    
    <list id="id1165024790817" list-type="bulleted"><title>Estimation by Rounding Fractions (<link document="m35014"/>)</title><item>be able to estimate the sum of two or more fractions using the technique of rounding fractions</item>
    </list>
